Organisers of the annual, travelling film industry awards, Best of Nollywood (BON), have announced plans to unveil the host city for the 2022 edition of the awards. In a statement signed by Seun Oloketuyi, founder BON Awards, the host city for the 14th edition would be announced on Tuesday, March 28 alongside presentation of hosting rights the the governor of the host state.   AFRIMA mourns former Ghanaian DJ RAB Bakari     Sikiru Ayinde Barrister: K1 consolidates Fuji…     Afrobeats not there yet, says Obi Asika   This event will officially kick-off of the activities that lead up to the award ceremony in the host city come Saturday, December 3, 2022. Over the years, the awards has sought to reward the best of Nigeria’s film industry, while keeping interests alive. Among, the 2021 nominees were Stan Nze, Femi Adebayo, Lateef Adedimeji; Sola Sobowale; Mercy Aigbe, Iyabo Ojo and others.